# AI-Business-OS Project Rules

## Start Here

Before any work, read [PROJECT_BRAIN.md](../../PROJECT_BRAIN.md) and follow [PROJECT_RULES.md](../../PROJECT_RULES.md).
Agent details: [AI/AGENT.md](../../AI/AGENT.md).

## Self-Documentation (required)

Every implementation must update docs when applicable:

- **Status changes** → [PROJECT_BRAIN.md](../../PROJECT_BRAIN.md)
- **New discoveries** → [LEARNINGS.md](../../LEARNINGS.md)
- **Architecture decisions** → new file in [adr/](../../adr/) + index in PROJECT_BRAIN

Do not finish a task without updating the relevant docs.

## Implementation

- Minimal scope — solve the task, nothing extra
- No duplication — one source of truth, link instead of repeat
- Match existing conventions before introducing patterns
- Stack changes on 🔒 list in TECH_STACK require an ADR first
- Check COSTS.md before adding AI calls or paid infra
- No secrets in repo

## Do Not

- Create README files unless explicitly requested
- Add placeholder or speculative content
- Edit accepted ADRs (supersede with new ADR)
- Edit PROJECT_RULES without explicit human approval
